# Spinor.Majorana

Majorana spinors and the Majorana condition.

A Majorana spinor is a Dirac spinor satisfying a reality condition:
  Ψ^c = Ψ  (charge conjugate equals self)

In (3+1) Lorentzian signature, Majorana spinors have 4 real degrees of freedom.
The Majorana condition is compatible with the Weyl condition only in dimensions
where both can be simultaneously imposed (not in 4D Lorentzian).

The connection to division algebras: in dimensions 3, 4, 6, 10 (related to
ℝ, ℂ, ℍ, 𝕆), Majorana–Weyl spinors exist and supersymmetry is enhanced.
This is the key observation in Baez–Huerta (arXiv:0909.0551).

